{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox school | name = Nehale Senior Secondary School | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = Nehale School Logo | motto = "Education crown of future" | established =1976 | opened = | type = Secondary School | district = Onayena | grades = 8–12 | superintendent = | principal = | viceprincipal = | viceprincipal_label = | enrollment = | faculty = Commerce, Science, Natural science and Social Studies | campus size = | colors = White, blue & black | location = [[Onayena Constituency]] | country = [[Namibia]] | coordinates = | information = | website = {{url|http://facebook.com/nehalehighschool}} | feeders = }}
'''Nehale Senior Secondary School''' is a public school in [[Onayena Constituency|Onayena]], [[Oshikoto Region]], Namibia. Established in 1976, it is the second oldest school in the region but also in the entire former [[Ovamboland]]. Nehale SSS is named after [[Nehale Mpingana]], king of the [[Ondonga]]. The school is located at [[Onayena]], approximately 20 kilometres east of [[Ondangwa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=28&tx_ttnews%5btt_news%5d=20971&no_cache=1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-10-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331214954/http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=28&tx_ttnews%5btt_news%5d=20971&no_cache=1 |archivedate=31 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
It has a history of exceptional performance with the highest pass rate in the region and the second best preferred school in the region after [[Oshigambo High School]]. Nehale Secondary School is also a cluster centre to the schools in [[Onayena Constituency|Onayena]].It is part of [[Onathinge]] education cluster. The school [[Head teacher|principal]] is Elifas Iimene.
==Current State== The school was established during the colonial era and has not seen major renovations since then. The school obtains most of its funding from the government. This is generally not sufficient to cover running school expenses. Its facilities are thus dilapidated. A broken sewerage system, lack of accommodation for teachers, inadequate laboratory facilities and the lack of a hall are the major challenges.<ref>{{Cite news | title=Northern school | last=Hilukilwa | first=Placido | newspaper = [[Namibian Sun]] | date=30 April 2012 | url=http://sun.com.na/content/national-news/northern-school}}</ref>
==Notable alumni== The following people have attended or taught at Nehale Senior Secondary: * [[Peya Mushelenga]], Deputy Minister of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Namibia * [[Johannes Nakwafila]], Namibian politician who served as [[SWAPO]] Party Councillor for [[Epembe Constituency]] * [[Tunakie]], Namibian multiple award-winning musician
